---
import Default from "../layouts/Default.astro";
---

<Default title="Install · Basalt" description="Install Basalt on every surface — CLI, plugin, MCP, desktop, web.">
  <section class="container">
    <span class="numeral">Install</span>
    <h1>Pick the surface that already fits your day.</h1>
    <p>
      Everything below installs the same engine. Run them side by side; they
      share the index database at <code>~/.basalt/</code>.
    </p>

    <h2>CLI</h2>
    <pre><code>npm install -g @basalt/cli
basalt init        # walks the vault, builds the index
basalt brief       # writes today's brief into the vault
basalt about       # prints version + bindings</code></pre>

    <p>
      <strong>v1.1.0 — LLM augmentation.</strong> Pass <code>--llm ollama</code>,
      <code>--llm openai</code>, or <code>--llm anthropic</code> to any brief
      command to get a synthesized one-sentence Implicit Thesis and an LLM
      verdict (<code>proven</code> / <code>apparent</code>) on each
      Contradiction. BYOK keys come from <code>OPENAI_API_KEY</code> /
      <code>ANTHROPIC_API_KEY</code> environment variables — never on disk.
    </p>
    <pre><code>basalt brief --llm ollama          # local; no key needed
basalt thesis --llm anthropic       # uses claude-sonnet-4-6 by default
basalt brief --llm openai --llm-model gpt-4o-mini</code></pre>

    <h2>Obsidian plugin</h2>
    <p>
      Open Obsidian → Settings → Community Plugins → Browse → search for
      <code>basalt</code>. The plugin reads your active vault and writes briefs
      into a configurable folder.
    </p>

    <h2>MCP server</h2>
    <p>For Claude Desktop, Cursor, and anything else that speaks MCP:</p>
    <pre><code>claude mcp add basalt -- npx -y @basalt/mcp</code></pre>
    <p>
      The MCP exposes six read-only verbs. Promote-to-note is intentionally
      absent from MCP — agents can describe a finding, but only humans turn it
      into a vault file.
    </p>

    <h2>Desktop</h2>
    <p>
      Single-binary downloads for macOS (Universal), Linux x64, Windows x64.
      Signed builds land at
      <a href="https://github.com/plsft/basalt/releases">github.com/plsft/basalt/releases</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Web cockpit</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="https://app.basalt.dev">app.basalt.dev</a> — Pro tier. Sign in
      with GitHub or Google, register a vault, generate briefs against your
      indexed corpus.
    </p>

    <h2>Verify</h2>
    <p>Every surface prints the same identity:</p>
    <pre><code>basalt about
# basalt 0.5.0
# core   0.5.0
# engine ok
# index  /Users/you/.basalt/db.sqlite</code></pre>
  </section>
</Default>
